                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15005408" author="tilman" created="Sat, 14 Nov 2015 14:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;asterisk.pdf is the user file. helloworld.pdf is mine, it was created with the HelloWorldTTF example, and these parameters:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;args = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[]{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;helloworld.pdf&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog !\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;#$%&amp;amp;&apos;()***+,-./0123456789:;&amp;lt;=&amp;gt;?@&quot;,
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;C:/windows/fonts/arial.ttf&quot;&lt;/span&gt;};        
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are three &quot;*&quot; after the &quot;()&quot;. These are shown as &apos; in Adobe Reader.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15013923" author="tilman" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2015 17:11:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stuff I found out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the &quot;*&quot; appears if the string also contains a &quot;&#223;&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the font has the symbolic flag. (why?) But changing the value to 32 (non symbolic) doesn&apos;t improve anything.&lt;br/&gt;
This is done in TrueTypeEmbedder.createFontDescriptor(). In the PDTrueTypeFontEmbedder constructor the opposite is done (earlier).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15014879" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 00:40:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The symbolic / nonsymbolic flags have no effect on CIDFonts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025011" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 18:12:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible idea: maybe it is because the asterisk (code 0D here) is not escaped. PDFDebugger shows a &quot;nice&quot; view, but not what&apos;s really in the content stream. In the hex view one can see that there is a 0D.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025042" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 18:25:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It works with a small change in COSWriter. I&apos;ll commit it after researching what else needs to be escaped. Currently we only use hex if there are &quot;negative&quot; bytes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025054" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 18:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;An end-of-line marker appearing within a literal string without a preceding REVERSE SOLIDUS shall be treated as a byte value of (0Ah), irrespective of whether the end-of-line marker was a CARRIAGE RETURN (0Dh), a LINE FEED (0Ah), or both.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;end-of-line marker (EOL marker)&lt;br/&gt;
one or two character sequence marking the end of a line of text, consisting of a CARRIAGE RETURN character (0Dh) or a LINE FEED character (0Ah) or a CARRIAGE RETURN followed immediately by a LINE FEED&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025090" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 18:48:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1716232 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1716232&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1716232&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3107&quot; title=&quot;Asterisk character not displaying properly in Adobe Reader&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3107&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3107&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025101" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 18:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commit msg changed to &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3107&quot; title=&quot;Asterisk character not displaying properly in Adobe Reader&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3107&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3107&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: escape if a string contains EOL markers&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025114" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 19:02:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Setting to resolved. I&apos;ll open a follow up issue about the correct parsing of strings with a EOL marker within after thinking about it in a quiet moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025214" author="mtnbiker987" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 19:51:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great fix!&lt;br/&gt;
I just built the latest snapshot, loaded it with my application, and the hollow boxes and/or single quotes are no longer replacing the asterisks in Adobe Reader.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any indication as to why only Adobe Reader was affected, and not the built-in viewers for Chrome and Firefox?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15025258" author="tilman" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 20:10:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chrome and Firefox do it wrong, that is why, i.e. they just read the 0d as a 0d instead of converting it to 0a as in the spec. Ghostscript did it correctly, i.e. your file looked bad. Ghostscript is very high quality, very close to Adobe Reader.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
